TSMC Says Chip Industry Growth to Be 4% This Year

-- B y   T i m   C u l p a n
-- 
2011-06-09T04:29:12Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-06-09/tsmc-says-chip-industry-growth-to-be-4-this-year-correct-.html
Taiwan Semiconductor Manufacturing
Co. expects chip industry growth to be 4 percent this year,
Chairman and Chief Executive Officer  Morris Chang  told reporters
after the Hsinchu, Taiwan-based company’s annual shareholders’
meeting.  The foundry sector is anticipated to climb 12 percent this
year, he said. The chip industry, when including memory
semiconductors, will expand 5 percent, Chang said.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Tim Culpan in Taipei at 
 tculpan1@bloomberg.net   To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Young-Sam Cho at 
 ycho2@bloomberg.net  